{
  "texts": [
    "If religious schooling has no negative effect on political tolerance, the outcome which is the toughest test for faith-based schools, it is difficult to imagine it has negative effects on any other civic outcome.",
    "We made efforts through unrestricted database searches and expansive citation and expert searches to reduce the possibility of publication bias.",
    "We coded for a variable that allowed us to rule out reporting bias as a problem.",
    "However, if the studies included in the dataset are a biased sample of all potentially relevant studies, then the calculated meta-analytic effect will also be biased (Borenstein et al., 2009, p. 277).",
    "Earlier results motivate us to test for the presence of publication bias for effect year < 1998."
  ]
}